<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The United States, Russia, and Ukraine will sign a 
tripartite agreement with regard to compensating Ukraine for the 
removal of its nuclear weapons and also security guarantees. 
This has been announced to journalists in Kiev by Ukraine 
President Leonid Kravchuk. 
  In his words, reports Interfax, this will be an agreement 
which will not affect the interests of any state. He also 
confirmed that 17 SS-24 missiles have been stood down from 
combat duty. The president said that they cannot be used, even 
by Russia. 

