<H3> <TI>   Kiev Dismantles SS-24 Nuclear Missiles </TI></H3>
<H4>   Announcement Made 20 December </H4>
<F P=102> AU2012173193 Paris AFP in English 1722 GMT 20 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> AU2012173193 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, Dec 20 (AFP) -- Ukraine is to dismantle almost 
half of the 46 SS-24 nuclear missiles in its nuclear arsenal 
inherited from the former Soviet Union, Deputy Prime Minister 
Valery Shmarov said Monday. 
  He said Ukraine would dismantle 20 of the 46 strategic 
missiles by the end of this month. 
  The decision comes only days after last week's meeting of 
top 
Ukrainian, Russian and U.S. officials. Until now Ukraine has 
refused to give up the weapons without security guarantees from 
the United States. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

