<H3> <TI>   Japan Reportedly To Assist Financing of Nuclear Disarmament </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1712122493 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 0845 GMT 17 Dec 93 </F>
<F P=103> LD1712122493 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Ukrainian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kiev [no date as receivedd] -- A UNIAN 
correspondent was informed at the Japanese Embassy in Ukraine 
that a working meeting of employees of the Foreign Ministries of 
Japan and Ukraine took place on 16 December about Japan's 
assistance in eliminating Ukrainian nuclear weapons. According 
to information of the embassy's secretary, Japan will finance 
nuclear disarmament of Ukraine, Belarus, Kazakhstan, and Russia 
irrespective of the assessments of the state's government or the 
manner of ratification of the START I Treaty by Ukraine. The 
total sum, which Japan is currently planning to spend on these 
four states comes to $100 million. But a final decision 
regarding Ukraine's share has not been adopted yet. 

</TEXT>

