<H3> <TI>   PJF Seizes Over Two Tons of Marijuana in 4 States </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  94WB0016D Mexico City EXCELSIOR in Spanish 5 Dec 93 pp 45-A, 
47-A </F>

<F P=103> 94WB0016D </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City EXCELSIOR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:CSO 

<F P=106> [Article by Rafael Medina Cruz] </F>
  [Excerpt] During the past few hours, dried and packed 
marijuana weighing over two tons was seized by Federal Judicial 
Police [PJF] agents in Sonora, Tamaulipas, Michoacan, and 
Sinaloa. A part of the shipment was detected on a tank truck, 
and another on the deck of a boat. These confiscations prompted 
the capture of at least five presumed drug traffickers. 
  In Hermosillo, Sonora, PJF agents seized a shipment 
consisting of a ton and 560 kg of cannabis indica on a tank 
truck presumably abandoned on the corner of 30th and 40th 
Streets. Based on the investigations, it was determined that the 
vehicle, with Federal Public Service plates 910-UD, owned by the 
Trans-Gas Company, had been left on the aforementioned site for 
three days, possibly awaiting the arrival of someone to retrieve 
it. 
  For the tank's inspection, part of the fuel that it 
contained 
had to be extracted first, so as to search the inside. There, 
166 packages of the drug, distributed in sacks, cardboard boxes, 
and plastic bags, were discovered. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

