<F P=100> EAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Narcotics Roundup for 27 Dec-2 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0301082194 </F>
<F P=103> BK0301082194 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on narcotics developments in South Asia, Southeast Asia, 
and the Pacific monitored by Bangkok Bureau between 27 December 
1993 and 2 January 1994. Source information is given in 
parentheses after each item. 
<H5>  Pakistan </H5>
<H5>  Nigerian Arrested on Heroin Charges at Karachi Airport </H5>
  The Customs Drug Enforcement Cell arrested Nigerian national 
Saliu Lasisi at Karachi's Quaid-e-Azam International Airport on 
25 December. The suspect was aboard an Ethiopian Airlines 
flight bound for Lagos via Addis Ababa. Officers found 4.2 kg 
of heroin powder concealed in cavities inside of 30 wooden 
hangers in his luggage. (Islamabad THE NATION in English 27 Dec 
93 p 12) 
<H5>  Peshawar Customs Seizes 8.25 Kg of Heroin </H5>
  Acting on a tip about a drug shipment, Peshawar Customs 
established a checkpoint near Hayatabad Chowk. When a vehicle 
attempted to avoid the checkpoint, the officers gave chase. The 
driver later abandoned the vehicle. Officers found 8.250 kg of 
heroin. (Peshawar THE FRONTIER POST in English 31 Dec 93 p 3) 
<H5>  Burma </H5>
<H5>  Officials Seize 10.319 Kg of Opium From Passenger Bus </H5>
  Officials from Defense Services Intelligence and the special 
antidrug squad stopped and searched a passenger bus at Lashio 
checkpoint on 10 November. They seized 10.319 kg of raw opium 
from two passengers. (Rangoon THE NEW LIGHT OF BURMA in English 
19 Nov 93 p 7) 
<H5>  Indonesia </H5>
<H5>  Police Seize 120 Kg of Marijuana, Arrest Two </H5>
  Police antinarcotics officers from Medan Precinct uncovered 
a 
drug syndicate on 30 December, seizing 12 bales of marijuana 
weighing 120 kg. Officers arrested a 43-year-old woman 
identified as S. BR. P., and a 35-year-old identified as Wah. 
They were caught while negotiating over the price of the 
marijuana, a police spokesman said. (Jakarta ANTARA in English 
1321 GMT 31 Dec 93) 

</TEXT>

