<F P=100> EAST ASIA </F>
<F P=101> THAILAND </F>
<H3> <TI>   American Citizen Arrested at Airport, 1.4 Kg of Heroin Seized </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK0301062994 Hong Kong AFP in English 0920 GMT 2 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK0301062994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bangkok, Jan 2 (AFP) -- An American man was arrested 
at Bangkok's international airport Sunday on charges of 
possessing and trafficking in heroin, an anti-narcotics official 
said. 
  Gregory Shaun Cooks, 33, of Austin, Texas, was arrested as 
he 
was about leave for Taiwan. The official said 1.4 kilograms (3.1 
pounds) of heroin were seized. 
  Convicted drug traffickers face the death penalty in 
Thailand 
but the sentence is usually commuted to a lengthy prison term. 
  About two-thirds of the 1,200 foreigners in Thai jails have 
been jailed for drug offences. 

</TEXT>

